The paper discusses the development of a Polystore database, which is a type of database that can store multiple data models and data types. This is a topic that falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of complex analytics and multiple programming languages, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The application of the Polystore database to an ocean metagenomics problem suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS) and computational biology (cs.CE).
